text: Florian Tuma (born 14 July 1977 in Vienna) is an Austrian former competitive figure skater. He is a five-time Austrian national champion (1993–1997) and competed in the final segment at six ISU Championships, including the 1995 World Championships in Birmingham, England, and 1996 European Championships in Sofia, Bulgaria. == Programs == {|class=wikitable style=text-align:center !
